results.name: Number of inseparable factorizations of n into factors > 1.
comment: A multiset is separable if it has a permutation that is an anti-run, meaning there are no adjacent equal parts.
xref: The version for partitions is A325535.
The version for multisets with prescribed multiplicities is A335126.
Separable partitions are ranked by A335433.
Inseparable partitions are ranked by A335448.
Anti-run permutations of prime indices are A335452.
Patterns contiguously matched by compositions are A335457.
